{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013yAnZKFNfmG7RocqZGTQvu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 11.2: Workflow Referential Integrity Validation\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want the workflow parser to validate that all referenced drivers and agents exist,\n11\tso that I get clear errors before execution if my workflow configuration is wrong.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a workflow YAML with `driver: codex` on a task\n16\t   **When** the workflow is parsed via `parseWorkflow()` or `resolveWorkflow()`\n17\t   **Then** the parser checks that `codex` is a registered driver name via the driver registry\n18\t   **And** if the driver is not registered, a `WorkflowParseError` is thrown listing the invalid driver name, the task name, and the set of registered drivers as a suggested fix\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** a workflow YAML with `agent: dev` on a task\n22\t   **When** the workflow is parsed via `parseWorkflow()` or `resolveWorkflow()`\n23\t   **Then** the parser checks that `dev` exists as an embedded agent template (file `templates/agents/dev.yaml` exists)\n24\t   **And** if the agent template does not exist, a `WorkflowParseError` is thrown listing the invalid agent name, the task name, and available agent templates as a suggested fix\n25\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t3. **Given** a workflow YAML with multiple tasks, where one has `driver: nonexistent` and another has `agent: fake-agent`\n28\t   **When** the workflow is parsed\n29\t   **Then** all referential integrity errors are collected and reported in a single `WorkflowParseError` (not fail-fast on the first error)\n30\t   **And** each error includes the field name (`driver` or `agent`), the task name, and the invalid value\n31\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t4. **Given** a workflow YAML with `driver: claude-code` on a task (a valid registered driver)\n34\t   **When** the workflow is parsed\n35\t   **Then** validation passes without error for that task's driver field\n36\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n37\t\n38\t5. **Given** a workflow YAML where no tasks specify a `driver` field\n39\t   **When** the workflow is parsed\n40\t   **Then** validation passes (driver field is optional; the engine defaults to `claude-code` at dispatch time)\n41\t   **And** no referential integrity check is performed for absent driver fields\n42\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n43\t\n44\t6. **Given** a workflow YAML where a task specifies an agent that exists as a project-level or user-level override (not just embedded)\n45\t   **When** the workflow is parsed\n46\t   **Then** the agent validation accepts it if the agent can be resolved via `resolveAgent()` (embedded, user-level, or project-level)\n47\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n48\t\n49\t7. **Given** referential integrity validation\n50\t   **When** it runs\n51\t   **Then** it executes at parse time, after schema validation but before the `ResolvedWorkflow` is returned\n52\t   **And** the existing flow-to-task referential integrity check (dangling task refs in flow) still runs\n53\t   **And** both check types (flow refs + driver/agent refs) report errors in the same `WorkflowParseError` if both fail\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t8. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n57\t   **When** the build completes\n58\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n59\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n60\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n61\t\n62\t9. **Given** unit tests for the referential integrity validation\n63\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n64\t   **Then** tests cover: valid driver passes, invalid driver fails with helpful error, valid agent passes, invalid agent fails with helpful error, multiple errors collected, absent driver/agent fields skip validation, backward compatibility with existing workflows\n65\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n68\t\n69\t- [x] Task 1: Add `listEmbeddedAgents()` utility to `agent-resolver.ts` (AC: #2, #6)\n70\t  - [x] Add `export function listEmbeddedAgents(): string[]` that reads `templates/agents/` directory and returns agent names (filenames without `.yaml` extension)\n71\t  - [x] This provides the \"available agents\" list for error messages without importing a hardcoded list\n72\t  - [x] Uses `readdirSync` on TEMPLATES_DIR, filters .yaml files, returns sorted names. Falls back to empty array on error.\n73\t\n74\t- [x] Task 2: Add `validateReferentialIntegrity()` function in `workflow-parser.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #7)\n75\t  - [x] Create a new internal function `validateReferentialIntegrity(data, taskNames, errors)` called after schema validation and after the existing flow-ref check\n76\t  - [x] For each task: if `driver` is defined and registry is populated, check `listDrivers()` from `factory.ts` — if not found, collect error\n77\t  - [x] For each task: if `agent` is defined, try `resolveAgent(agent)` — if not found, collect error with available agents list\n78\t  - [x] Combine all collected errors with any existing dangling-ref errors\n79\t  - [x] Throw single `WorkflowParseError` if any errors exist\n80\t\n81\t- [x] Task 3: Integrate validation into `validateAndResolve()` (AC: #4, #5, #7)\n82\t  - [x] Call `validateReferentialIntegrity()` after the existing flow-ref block but before building resolved tasks\n83\t  - [x] Merge dangling-ref errors and integrity errors into one error list before throwing\n84\t  - [x] Ensure absent `driver`/`agent` fields are skipped (only validate if present)\n85\t\n86\t- [x] Task 4: Handle driver registry initialization concern (AC: #1, #4)\n87\t  - [x] Option A implemented: validate only when `listDrivers().length > 0`, skip driver check if registry is empty\n88\t  - [x] Parse can be called independently of engine startup without false positives\n89\t\n90\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #8, #9)\n91\t  - [x] Test: workflow with `driver: claude-code` and registered driver passes validation\n92\t  - [x] Test: workflow with `driver: nonexistent` throws `WorkflowParseError` with driver name, task name, and registered drivers\n93\t  - [x] Test: workflow with `agent: dev` (valid embedded agent) passes validation\n94\t  - [x] Test: workflow with `agent: nonexistent-agent` throws `WorkflowParseError` with agent name, task name, and available agents\n95\t  - [x] Test: workflow with multiple invalid refs collects all errors in one throw\n96\t  - [x] Test: workflow with no `driver` field on any task passes (optional field)\n97\t  - [x] Test: existing flow-ref checks still work (regression guard)\n98\t  - [x] Test: backward compatibility — existing test workflows parse without errors\n99\t  - [x] 12 new tests added, all passing. 4350 total tests pass.\n100\t\n101\t## Dev Notes\n102\t\n103\t### Architecture Compliance\n104\t\n105\tThis story implements Epic 2 (mapped to sprint Epic 11), Story 2.2 \"Workflow Referential Integrity Validation\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers FR14 (workflow YAML referential integrity: all referenced drivers exist, all referenced agents exist).\n106\t\n107\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n108\t- **Decision 1 (Driver Interface):** `driver` field names match `AgentDriver.name` values registered in the factory. This story validates that contract at parse time.\n109\t- **Architecture Boundary:** The workflow parser boundary is extended to validate cross-module references (drivers via factory, agents via resolver) without importing driver internals.\n110\t\n111\t### Current State of the Codebase\n112\t\n113\t- **`workflow-parser.ts`** already has flow-to-task referential integrity checking (lines 73-103). The new validation follows the same pattern: collect errors, throw once.\n114\t- **`factory.ts`** exports `listDrivers(): string[]` which returns registered driver names. Currently only `claude-code` is registered (by `workflow-engine.ts` at startup). The registry may be empty at standalone parse time.\n115\t- **`agent-resolver.ts`** exports `loadEmbeddedAgent(name)` which throws `AgentResolveError` if the agent doesn't exist. No listing function exists yet — must be added.\n116\t- **Embedded agent templates** live in `templates/agents/`: `dev`, `qa`, `architect`, `pm`, `sm`, `analyst`, `ux-designer`, `tech-writer`, `evaluator`.\n117\t- **`ResolvedTask`** already includes optional `driver?: string` and `model?: string` and `plugins?: string[]` from story 11-1.\n118\t- **`WorkflowParseError`** already carries structured errors as `Array<{ path: string; message: string }>` — the new validation produces errors in the same format.\n119\t\n120\t### What NOT to Do\n121\t\n122\t- Do NOT validate `model` field values — model resolution happens at dispatch time via `model-resolver.ts` and depends on runtime context (driver defaults, agent configs)\n123\t- Do NOT validate `plugins` values — plugin availability depends on the driver and runtime environment\n124\t- Do NOT modify `factory.ts` or any driver files — only consume `listDrivers()`\n125\t- Do NOT modify the JSON schema — the schema validates structure, this story validates semantic references\n126\t- Do NOT make driver validation fail when the registry is empty — parse can be called independently of engine startup (test scenarios, CLI validation commands)\n127\t- Do NOT import driver classes directly — use the registry API only\n128\t\n129\t### Import Strategy\n130\t\n131\tThe `validateAndResolve()` function in `workflow-parser.ts` will need new imports:\n132\t- `import { listDrivers } from './agents/drivers/factory.js';` — for driver name validation\n133\t- A new `listEmbeddedAgents` function or `resolveAgent` from `./agent-resolver.js` — for agent name validation\n134\t\n135\tKeep imports minimal. Prefer checking file existence over loading/parsing full agent configs.\n136\t\n137\t### Error Message Format\n138\t\n139\tFollow the existing pattern from `factory.ts` `getDriver()`:\n140\t```\n141\tDriver 'codex' not found. Registered drivers: claude-code\n142\t```\n143\t\n144\tFor agents:\n145\t```\n146\tAgent 'fake-agent' not found in task 'implement'. Available agents: dev, qa, architect, pm, sm, analyst, ux-designer, tech-writer, evaluator\n147\t```\n148\t\n149\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n150\t\n151\tFrom story 11-1 (Workflow Schema Extension):\n152\t- `driver`, `model`, and `plugins` fields were added to both `workflow.schema.json` and `ResolvedTask` interface\n153\t- Forward-compat type casts in `workflow-engine.ts` were cleaned up\n154\t- The parser already populates `resolved.driver`, `resolved.model`, `resolved.plugins` from parsed YAML\n155\t- Story 11-1 explicitly deferred referential integrity to this story (11-2): \"Do NOT add referential integrity checks for `driver` values (that's story 11-2)\"\n156\t- Test patterns: write YAML to temp dir via `writeYaml()` helper, call `parseWorkflow()`, assert on `ResolvedTask` fields or expect `WorkflowParseError`\n157\t\n158\t### Git Intelligence\n159\t\n160\tRecent commits (all in current sprint):\n161\t- `a4bf7e6` — story 11-1: workflow schema extension (driver/model/plugins on tasks)\n162\t- `f128064` — story 10-5: workflow engine driver integration\n163\t- `3717741` — story 10-4: model resolution module\n164\t- `bd3f35d` — story 10-3: ClaudeCodeDriver extraction\n165\t- `48d0524` — story 10-2: driver factory & registry\n166\t\n167\tAll recent work is in the driver/workflow area. The codebase patterns are fresh and consistent.\n168\t\n169\t### Project Structure Notes\n170\t\n171\tFiles to modify:\n172\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — add `validateReferentialIntegrity()`, integrate into `validateAndResolve()`\n173\t- `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — add `listEmbeddedAgents()` utility\n174\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` — new test cases for referential integrity\n175\t\n176\tFiles NOT to modify:\n177\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts` — consume only, don't change\n178\t- `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` — schema validates structure, not semantic refs\n179\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/types.ts` — unchanged\n180\t- `src/lib/agents/model-resolver.ts` — unchanged\n181\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — unchanged (it registers drivers before parsing)\n182\t\n183\t### Testing Patterns\n184\t\n185\t- Follow existing patterns in `workflow-parser.test.ts`: write YAML to temp dir, call `parseWorkflow()`, assert on result\n186\t- Use existing `writeYaml()` helper\n187\t- For validation failures, expect `WorkflowParseError` to be thrown with specific error messages\n188\t- For driver registry tests: call `registerDriver()` with mock drivers before parsing, call `resetDrivers()` in afterEach\n189\t- For agent tests: rely on embedded templates existing at known paths (they do in test environment)\n190\t- Verify backward compatibility: all existing tests must continue to pass\n191\t\n192\t### References\n193\t\n194\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 2.2: Workflow Referential Integrity Validation]\n195\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 1: Driver Interface Design]\n196\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — validateAndResolve(), existing flow-ref integrity check]\n197\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts — listDrivers(), getDriver()]\n198\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — loadEmbeddedAgent(), TEMPLATES_DIR]\n199\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-1-workflow-schema-extension.md — previous story context]\n200\t\n201\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n202\t## Verification Requirements\n203\t\n204\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/11-2-workflow-referential-integrity-validation-proof.md)\n205\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n206\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n207\t\n208\t## Documentation Requirements\n209\t\n210\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n211\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/11-2-workflow-referential-integrity-validation.md\n212\t\n213\t## Testing Requirements\n214\t\n215\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n216\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n217\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n218\t\n219\t## Dev Agent Record\n220\t\n221\t### Agent Model Used\n222\t\n223\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n224\t\n225\t### Debug Log References\n226\t\n227\tN/A\n228\t\n229\t### Completion Notes List\n230\t\n231\t- All 5 tasks completed\n232\t- 12 new unit tests added covering all ACs\n233\t- 8 existing tests updated for new unified error message format and valid agent names\n234\t- Build: zero TypeScript errors\n235\t- Tests: 4350 passed, 0 failed (164 test files)\n236\t- Option A chosen for driver registry concern: skip validation when registry empty\n237\t\n238\t### File List\n239\t\n240\t- `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — added `listEmbeddedAgents()` export, added `readdirSync` import\n241\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — added `validateReferentialIntegrity()` function, integrated into `validateAndResolve()`, added imports for `listDrivers`, `listEmbeddedAgents`, `resolveAgent`\n242\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` — 12 new tests in \"referential integrity validation\" describe block, 8 existing tests updated for new error message format and valid agent names\n243\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RMnci4JBW5N3n4PYpHDPEs","session_id":"576f74f4-0d7f-4316-a569-4c3ab5c122fd","uuid":"775ae08e-396d-4343-90fc-e296801fa59d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:50:50.358Z"}
