 `loadWorkflowPatch` silently swallowed EACCES permission errors. Now throws on permission errors, null only for missing files.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Empty catch clause in embedded workflow loading discarded original error message.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** No test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'custom' })` path. Added.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `deepMerge` duplicated in agent-resolver.ts and workflow-parser.ts.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Custom workflow detection re-reads file that `parseWorkflow` also reads (minor I/O waste).\n- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — verification (2026-04-03T02:58)\n\n- **Proof format mismatch:** First proof used `### AC N:` (h3) instead of `## AC N:` (h2) and lacked bash/output block pairs. Rewrote.\n- **Warnings:** Showboat not installed, no exec-plan — non-blocking.\n- **BATS integration tests:** All show exit code 127 (pre-existing, unrelated).\n- **Branch coverage 79.12%:** Below 80% for branches specifically, but AC says \"80%+ coverage\" without specifying branches. Statement 93.96%, functions 100%.\n- All 10/10 ACs passed with real evidence.\n\n## Token Report — verification\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test | tail -80` (~80 lines), `vitest run workflow-parser.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (~45 lines)\n- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n- Redundant operations: vitest coverage run twice, npm run test:unit run twice\n\n### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — create-story (2026-04-03T07:06)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** The epic's ACs for story 9.2 are sparse (3 lines). Expanded to 10 ACs covering error paths, backward compatibility, edge cases (custom + patch coexistence), and agent resolution.\n- **Story is smaller than expected:** Most heavy lifting done in story 9-1. resolveWorkflow() already accepts a `name` parameter and detects full custom workflows. This story is primarily CLI plumbing + test coverage.\n- **Risk — user-level custom workflows unsupported:** resolveWorkflow() only checks project-level for full custom workflows. User-level custom workflows are only supported as patches, not full workflows.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 6, Edit: 0, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 5\n- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Two separate Glob calls for same pattern — minor\n\n### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — dev-story (2026-04-03T07:10)\n\nNo issues reported. Clean implementation — existing resolveWorkflow() already supported the name parameter.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Glob: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~80 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — code-review (2026-04-03T07:15)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** Path traversal vulnerability via `--workflow` CLI flag — no input sanitization allowed `../` sequences to escape `.codeharness/workflows/` directory. Fixed with regex validation.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Wrong error variable in `run.ts` fallback catch block (`err` → `fallbackErr`).\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Test assertions strengthened for `cwd` and error message content.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicate test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'nonexistent' })` between 9.2 section and pre-existing test.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Legacy fallback path in run.ts should eventually be removed.\n- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit